1
00:00:12,117 --> 00:00:14,494
Kick the murderer out!

2
00:00:14,577 --> 00:00:15,995
Kick him out!

3
00:00:16,079 --> 00:00:18,581
What did our kids do to deserve this?

4
00:00:18,665 --> 00:00:20,375
What did our kids do?

5
00:00:20,458 --> 00:00:22,377
Isolate the murderer!

6
00:00:22,460 --> 00:00:24,838
Isolate him!

7
00:00:24,921 --> 00:00:26,214
It's Cho Gyu-cheol!

8
00:00:26,297 --> 00:00:28,967
-Bastard! How dare you come here!
-Cho Gyu-cheol!

9
00:00:29,050 --> 00:00:30,593
-Look over here!
-You're not human!

10
00:00:30,677 --> 00:00:31,761
Drop out, you bastard!

11
00:00:32,345 --> 00:00:34,764
-How dare you go in!
-This is outrageous!

12
00:00:34,848 --> 00:00:36,641
Kick him out, for God's sake!

13
00:00:36,724 --> 00:00:40,812
You expect our kids to go to school
with him? Kick him out!

14
00:00:42,147 --> 00:00:44,691
<i>Cho Gyu-cheol has shown</i>
<i>deep remorse for his crimes,</i>

15
00:00:44,774 --> 00:00:49,279
<i>followed the correctional facility rules,</i>
<i>and set an example for others.</i>

16
00:00:49,904 --> 00:00:52,282
<i>Given his minor status and clean record,</i>

17
00:00:52,365 --> 00:00:57,287
<i>the committee finds no risk of recidivism</i>
<i>and hereby grants parole.</i>

18
00:01:24,314 --> 00:01:25,773
What do you think, sir?

19
00:01:26,733 --> 00:01:28,610
I'm talking about Cho Gyu-cheol.

20
00:01:33,114 --> 00:01:36,618
He was paroled
as soon as he completed his minimum term.

21
00:01:36,701 --> 00:01:38,995
When the Educational Rights Committee
signed off,

22
00:01:39,078 --> 00:01:41,998
they approved his readmission
almost instantly.

23
00:01:42,081 --> 00:01:44,959
Everything lining up perfectly,
as if planned, feels off.

24
00:01:45,043 --> 00:01:47,795
It's worth looking into, isn't it?

25
00:01:48,296 --> 00:01:50,423
Readmission
is at the principal's discretion.

26
00:01:51,382 --> 00:01:53,343
Cho Gyu-cheol has already been punished,

27
00:01:53,426 --> 00:01:57,889
and the ERPB has no authority to deny
a student the chance to return to school.

28
00:02:00,308 --> 00:02:01,851
If I stopped him…

29
00:02:05,188 --> 00:02:06,606
that would be revenge.

30
00:02:10,652 --> 00:02:11,611
Where's Inspector Na?

31
00:02:11,694 --> 00:02:14,280
He had to stop by somewhere
before coming in.

32
00:02:16,991 --> 00:02:17,992
Where?

33
00:03:03,621 --> 00:03:07,750
TEACH YOU A LESSON

34
00:03:08,543 --> 00:03:10,545
You look good in your uniform, don't you?

35
00:03:12,714 --> 00:03:14,215
Don't be nervous.

36
00:03:14,299 --> 00:03:16,467
I'm here as an ERPB inspector today.

37
00:03:17,427 --> 00:03:18,928
You're a test case

38
00:03:19,429 --> 00:03:22,015
to see if kids like you
can handle school again,

39
00:03:22,098 --> 00:03:24,058
if rehabilitation is possible,

40
00:03:24,142 --> 00:03:25,601
and if you deserve

41
00:03:26,477 --> 00:03:28,980
another chance.

42
00:03:31,399 --> 00:03:32,358
I will

43
00:03:33,401 --> 00:03:34,569
really do my best.

44
00:03:34,652 --> 00:03:37,113
No, just don't do anything.

45
00:03:37,196 --> 00:03:39,240
Just breathe and live quietly.

46
00:03:39,741 --> 00:03:40,867
Live a normal life.

47
00:03:43,036 --> 00:03:44,537
Live like a student.

48
00:03:51,044 --> 00:03:52,879
I'm sure you know what I mean.

49
00:04:15,068 --> 00:04:16,944
This is Cho Gyu-cheol,
back in school today.

50
00:04:17,028 --> 00:04:19,489
He's older than you, so be nice.

51
00:04:20,406 --> 00:04:22,367
-Say hi.
-Okay.

52
00:04:23,659 --> 00:04:26,579
I'll make sure
I don't get in the way of your studies.

53
00:04:28,247 --> 00:04:29,499
Nice to meet you.

54
00:04:37,215 --> 00:04:38,049
What?

55
00:04:38,132 --> 00:04:40,176
-Jong-su.
-What, dumbass?

56
00:04:41,511 --> 00:04:42,970
How could you… to a teacher…

57
00:04:44,597 --> 00:04:46,766
Seong-gu, call 119, for fuck's sake!

58
00:04:46,849 --> 00:04:48,434
Hey, stab him again.

59
00:04:48,976 --> 00:04:50,353
Damn, you're no fun.

60
00:04:50,436 --> 00:04:51,813
Hey.

61
00:04:52,730 --> 00:04:54,690
I heard you killed someone.

62
00:04:54,774 --> 00:04:56,192
A teacher, no less.

63
00:04:58,069 --> 00:05:01,030
Wow, fucking hell.
Check out the look in his eyes.

64
00:05:02,323 --> 00:05:03,533
You gonna kill me too?

65
00:05:09,330 --> 00:05:11,707
A goddamn murderer, studying?

66
00:05:15,670 --> 00:05:19,173
You feel this is unfair?
You want me to speak politely to you?

67
00:05:20,258 --> 00:05:22,468
No, it's fine. Speak however you want.

68
00:05:23,970 --> 00:05:25,471
Damn, you're chill.

69
00:05:25,555 --> 00:05:26,472
Behave yourself.

70
00:05:26,556 --> 00:05:30,226
If you act up and the ERPB shows up,
you'll be in trouble too.

71
00:05:31,227 --> 00:05:32,145
Get it?

72
00:05:33,646 --> 00:05:36,065
Yeah, I will. Thanks for the advice.

73
00:05:36,649 --> 00:05:38,276
What the hell? Let's go.

74
00:05:38,860 --> 00:05:39,986
Cigs.

75
00:05:40,069 --> 00:05:41,446
Cigs.

76
00:05:42,029 --> 00:05:43,656
-What a loser.
-Hey, are you coming?

77
00:05:43,739 --> 00:05:44,866
Yeah, coming.

78
00:06:07,388 --> 00:06:14,395
RESTRICTED AREA
AUTHORIZED PERSONNEL ONLY

79
00:06:30,161 --> 00:06:32,038
It's hilarious seeing him act all shy.

80
00:06:32,121 --> 00:06:33,664
Hey, show me the picture.

81
00:06:33,748 --> 00:06:34,749
Shit, I got a text.

82
00:06:35,249 --> 00:06:36,083
Here, look.

83
00:06:41,797 --> 00:06:42,882
That looks good too.

84
00:06:43,382 --> 00:06:44,884
-Holy shit, hold on.
-Why?

85
00:06:45,551 --> 00:06:46,511
I got an S-class.

86
00:06:47,011 --> 00:06:48,679
Screw you.

87
00:06:48,763 --> 00:06:50,681
MINISTRY OF EDUCATION

88
00:06:50,765 --> 00:06:52,642
Oh man, this is insane.

89
00:06:52,725 --> 00:06:53,809
What's the matter?

90
00:06:53,893 --> 00:06:56,145
It's a report about a student
assaulting a teacher

91
00:06:56,229 --> 00:06:58,439
after being told not to use their phone.

92
00:06:58,523 --> 00:07:00,816
He challenged the teacher
under Yatcha rules.

93
00:07:00,900 --> 00:07:02,610
Yatcha rules? What's that?

94
00:07:03,444 --> 00:07:06,614
It's a bare-knuckle fight.
No rank, no rules.

95
00:07:06,697 --> 00:07:08,491
We're doing everything we can,

96
00:07:08,574 --> 00:07:10,576
yet things like this keep happening.

97
00:07:12,954 --> 00:07:14,622
What are you doing out there? Come in.

98
00:07:15,122 --> 00:07:17,166
Someone is here to see you.

99
00:07:17,250 --> 00:07:18,125
Bring them in.

100
00:07:19,043 --> 00:07:19,877
Okay.

101
00:07:47,947 --> 00:07:48,906
Right.

102
00:07:50,575 --> 00:07:52,785
What brings you here?

103
00:07:53,911 --> 00:07:55,246
I have something to tell you.

104
00:07:56,163 --> 00:07:58,082
You've got some nerve coming here!

105
00:07:58,583 --> 00:08:00,751
This is the ERPB.

106
00:08:00,835 --> 00:08:03,796
Any student can come here.

107
00:08:04,380 --> 00:08:05,381
Have a seat.

108
00:08:14,682 --> 00:08:16,601
So what brings you here?

109
00:08:17,560 --> 00:08:19,604
I'm here to report bullying at school.

110
00:08:21,689 --> 00:08:24,150
Ms. Choi once told me

111
00:08:24,650 --> 00:08:26,819
that looking out
for others who are struggling

112
00:08:26,902 --> 00:08:28,863
is something students should also learn.

113
00:08:28,946 --> 00:08:30,990
How dare you say her name!

114
00:08:31,073 --> 00:08:32,199
Inspector Im Han-rim.

115
00:08:32,283 --> 00:08:34,160
Aren't any of you angry?

116
00:08:34,660 --> 00:08:36,078
Inspector Im Han-rim.

117
00:08:36,162 --> 00:08:38,164
Go outside and get some air.

118
00:08:38,664 --> 00:08:39,498
Okay?

119
00:08:40,958 --> 00:08:42,293
Come on, let's go.

120
00:08:45,796 --> 00:08:46,631
All right.

121
00:08:51,469 --> 00:08:52,970
Finish what you were saying.

122
00:08:54,138 --> 00:08:57,058
I'm sorry for bringing up Ms. Choi's name.

123
00:09:06,359 --> 00:09:08,611
This is the kid getting bullied.

124
00:09:14,200 --> 00:09:16,786
<i>He's definitely up to something.</i>

125
00:09:17,286 --> 00:09:20,956
But the information he gave us
was pretty specific.

126
00:09:21,749 --> 00:09:22,583
He's right.

127
00:09:22,667 --> 00:09:25,628
Cho Gyu-cheol isn't an exception.
We'll do as we always have.

128
00:09:26,212 --> 00:09:28,881
Deputy Director Bong Geun-dae,
this case is yours.

129
00:09:29,465 --> 00:09:31,801
-Yes, sir.
-No, I'll go.

130
00:09:32,677 --> 00:09:34,679
You can't, sir. Instead, I will--

131
00:09:34,762 --> 00:09:37,098
Is there a reason why I can't go?

132
00:09:39,600 --> 00:09:40,601
Stop him, won't you?

133
00:09:41,435 --> 00:09:42,520
Should I stop you?

134
00:09:43,562 --> 00:09:45,231
Stop the traffic instead.

135
00:09:46,816 --> 00:09:48,192
-Oh dear.
-I'm sorry.

136
00:09:49,985 --> 00:09:53,614
Don't even think about
telling any jokes, anywhere.

137
00:09:55,157 --> 00:09:56,117
Get going.

138
00:09:56,200 --> 00:09:57,034
Okay.

139
00:09:57,118 --> 00:10:00,496
-You shouldn't laugh at his jokes.
-I'll see you later.

140
00:10:00,996 --> 00:10:01,914
Deputy Bong.

141
00:10:02,415 --> 00:10:03,708
Oh, come on. Not now.

142
00:10:04,375 --> 00:10:07,002
Don't try to stop me. I'm not traffic.

143
00:10:07,962 --> 00:10:09,380
I laughed. I'm so annoyed.

144
00:10:09,463 --> 00:10:10,715
What's wrong with…

145
00:10:10,798 --> 00:10:12,425
-I'm sorry, Minister.
-Don't laugh.

146
00:10:12,508 --> 00:10:13,801
You shouldn't laugh.

147
00:10:14,301 --> 00:10:15,302
Oh man, I laughed.

148
00:10:24,520 --> 00:10:25,813
JINWON HIGH SCHOOL

149
00:10:25,896 --> 00:10:27,314
<i>Jang Seong-gu from my class?</i>

150
00:10:28,315 --> 00:10:30,359
Seong-gu is being bullied?

151
00:10:33,112 --> 00:10:35,740
He didn't seem to have any problems
from the outside.

152
00:10:36,323 --> 00:10:37,616
<i>He has a lot of friends,</i>

153
00:10:37,700 --> 00:10:42,121
<i>and Seong-gu himself said</i>
<i>he was enjoying school.</i>

154
00:10:42,747 --> 00:10:44,540
We'll sing "Emergency Room" at karaoke.

155
00:10:44,623 --> 00:10:46,292
-No.
-What?

156
00:10:47,668 --> 00:10:49,420
Stop stuffing your face with my chips.

157
00:10:49,503 --> 00:10:50,546
Okay.

158
00:10:52,673 --> 00:10:53,758
That's lit.

159
00:10:54,383 --> 00:10:56,677
-What the…
-Hey, what's going on?

160
00:10:57,344 --> 00:10:58,554
Why is it lagging?

161
00:11:01,223 --> 00:11:02,516
Where did Jang Seong-gu go?

162
00:11:06,896 --> 00:11:09,607
Why are you nervous? Did I scare you?

163
00:11:10,107 --> 00:11:11,108
Well…

164
00:11:11,776 --> 00:11:13,152
You're from the ERPB.

165
00:11:13,235 --> 00:11:14,403
Yeah.

166
00:11:14,904 --> 00:11:16,071
Do you know why I'm here?

167
00:11:16,155 --> 00:11:17,907
No, I don't.

168
00:11:17,990 --> 00:11:20,451
We were tipped off
that someone was being bullied.

169
00:11:21,452 --> 00:11:22,995
That doesn't happen here.

170
00:11:24,079 --> 00:11:24,955
Excuse me.

171
00:11:27,416 --> 00:11:28,250
Let's see.

172
00:11:30,419 --> 00:11:31,879
-Say, "Ah."
-What?

173
00:11:31,962 --> 00:11:33,047
Come on, say, "Ah."

174
00:11:36,967 --> 00:11:38,427
At least you weren't hit.

175
00:11:38,511 --> 00:11:40,805
Oh man, it's not me.

176
00:11:41,388 --> 00:11:42,848
I'll be on my way.

177
00:11:43,432 --> 00:11:44,809
Are you Wi-Fi?

178
00:11:47,645 --> 00:11:51,524
Do you turn your hotspot on so the kids
can use their phones and play games?

179
00:11:52,441 --> 00:11:53,734
Are you a human Wi-Fi?

180
00:11:56,529 --> 00:11:59,740
You're always at the center,
like people gathering around Wi-Fi.

181
00:11:59,824 --> 00:12:02,868
<i>And you're always the first one</i>
<i>to take out your phone.</i>

182
00:12:02,952 --> 00:12:04,787
<i>You probably do that</i>

183
00:12:04,870 --> 00:12:07,998
<i>to turn your hotspot on</i>
<i>so they can connect to Wi-Fi.</i>

184
00:12:09,375 --> 00:12:12,837
Also, you're the only one
carrying around that huge power bank.

185
00:12:13,337 --> 00:12:15,422
You can't let the Wi-Fi go down, can you?

186
00:12:22,137 --> 00:12:24,014
I'm really not a human Wi-Fi.

187
00:12:24,557 --> 00:12:26,809
But seriously, I really have to go.

188
00:12:26,892 --> 00:12:28,727
I'll be going now. Yeah.

189
00:12:30,187 --> 00:12:31,480
Hey, the punk's here.

190
00:12:31,564 --> 00:12:34,024
Hey, Jang Seong-gu.
What are you doing here?

191
00:12:34,108 --> 00:12:35,359
Well, a moment ago…

192
00:12:35,442 --> 00:12:37,945
I was just walking, and the ERPB…

193
00:12:38,028 --> 00:12:40,489
Holy fuck. It's the ERPB.

194
00:12:40,573 --> 00:12:42,116
Watch your language.

195
00:12:42,199 --> 00:12:44,285
What's the ERPB doing at our school?

196
00:12:45,035 --> 00:12:46,412
Fuck, I know.

197
00:12:46,495 --> 00:12:47,705
Is it Cho Gyu-cheol?

198
00:12:47,788 --> 00:12:49,373
No, I'm here because of you.

199
00:12:49,456 --> 00:12:50,958
I heard you're a bully.

200
00:12:51,584 --> 00:12:53,460
-Me?
-Yeah.

201
00:12:55,212 --> 00:12:56,755
Who did I bully?

202
00:12:56,839 --> 00:12:59,717
I told you no!

203
00:12:59,800 --> 00:13:03,220
Please don't accuse innocent people.
It's really not like that!

204
00:13:03,304 --> 00:13:06,098
Why are you upsetting our sweet Seong-gu?

205
00:13:06,181 --> 00:13:08,142
Seong-gu, that's enough, man.

206
00:13:08,225 --> 00:13:10,185
The ERPB can make mistakes too.

207
00:13:12,021 --> 00:13:13,063
Can we go now?

208
00:13:13,772 --> 00:13:14,773
Sure.

209
00:13:14,857 --> 00:13:16,984
-Okay. Goodbye, sir.
-Yeah.

210
00:13:17,610 --> 00:13:18,444
Let's go.

211
00:13:19,278 --> 00:13:22,448
Hey, you scared me there.
I thought you'd vanished.

212
00:13:22,531 --> 00:13:23,991
Were you here all along?

213
00:13:24,491 --> 00:13:26,201
Why are you all sweaty, Seong-gu?

214
00:13:28,996 --> 00:13:30,414
Hey, squad up.

215
00:13:30,497 --> 00:13:31,665
I got a legendary item.

216
00:13:33,459 --> 00:13:34,543
Don't engage now.

217
00:13:34,627 --> 00:13:35,544
-Stay back.
-Okay.

218
00:13:36,670 --> 00:13:37,671
Bong Geun-dae?

219
00:13:39,506 --> 00:13:41,675
Hey, you're Geun-dae, right?
Bong Geun-dae.

220
00:13:41,759 --> 00:13:44,637
-Yeah. Yes.
-It's been ages. How are you?

221
00:13:44,720 --> 00:13:47,264
Yeah, I'm good. What about you?

222
00:13:47,348 --> 00:13:50,893
I heard you're a civil servant.
I think I heard where you worked.

223
00:13:51,393 --> 00:13:52,353
The ERPB? Right?

224
00:13:52,436 --> 00:13:53,562
-The ERPB.
-Wait.

225
00:13:53,646 --> 00:13:54,772
-Hold on.
-Good for you.

226
00:13:54,855 --> 00:13:56,857
I'll call you later.

227
00:13:56,941 --> 00:13:57,900
Sorry.

228
00:13:57,983 --> 00:13:59,485
Wait, Bong Geun-dae.

229
00:13:59,568 --> 00:14:01,987
-One of you, get in here.
-Hold on.

230
00:14:02,071 --> 00:14:03,822
-Hey, we should go.
-Yeah, after this.

231
00:14:03,906 --> 00:14:05,032
-A bit more.
-Group up.

232
00:14:05,115 --> 00:14:06,116
Yeah, okay.

233
00:14:13,499 --> 00:14:14,792
That was fast. Got the audio?

234
00:14:14,875 --> 00:14:16,877
-Wait a minute.
-Why?

235
00:14:17,503 --> 00:14:19,421
-I messed up.
-What?

236
00:14:19,505 --> 00:14:20,464
Put these on.

237
00:14:20,547 --> 00:14:21,882
-Here.
-Why should I?

238
00:14:22,925 --> 00:14:24,468
-What are you doing?
-Hold on.

239
00:14:24,551 --> 00:14:25,511
I failed. Stay still.

240
00:14:26,679 --> 00:14:28,138
Put this in your right ear.

241
00:14:28,222 --> 00:14:30,099
-Isn't this that thing?
-An earpiece.

242
00:14:30,182 --> 00:14:31,725
-Isn't this eyeshadow?
-Yeah.

243
00:14:31,809 --> 00:14:33,602
-What are you…
-Hold still.

244
00:14:35,771 --> 00:14:36,772
It's done.

245
00:14:37,272 --> 00:14:38,482
Just remember one thing.

246
00:14:38,565 --> 00:14:41,443
A loser never makes eye contact.

247
00:14:42,069 --> 00:14:43,028
A loser?

248
00:14:46,198 --> 00:14:48,075
Fucking hell. What?

249
00:14:48,158 --> 00:14:50,452
Let's just go, idiot. Something feels off.

250
00:14:50,536 --> 00:14:54,081
-What the hell, dumbass?
-You're a fucking noob anyway. Let's go.

251
00:14:54,581 --> 00:14:55,416
I said let's go.

252
00:15:00,879 --> 00:15:02,131
Fuck, what are you doing?

253
00:15:03,340 --> 00:15:04,758
Are you freaking blind or what?

254
00:15:05,384 --> 00:15:06,510
<i>Look down.</i>

255
00:15:09,555 --> 00:15:11,098
You're fucking lucky.

256
00:15:11,181 --> 00:15:12,433
Don't let me see you again.

257
00:15:12,516 --> 00:15:14,601
Quit acting dumb and fuck off, damn it.

258
00:15:18,397 --> 00:15:19,898
It's because you flipped out.

259
00:15:19,982 --> 00:15:22,276
<i>Inspector Im Han-rim,</i>
<i>good job holding back.</i>

260
00:15:22,359 --> 00:15:24,570
Damn it, that fucking bastard.

261
00:15:27,865 --> 00:15:29,992
Is it done? Testing.

262
00:15:31,952 --> 00:15:34,121
I'm done cloning Lee Chi-ho's voice.

263
00:15:34,204 --> 00:15:35,456
-Let's check it out.
-Okay.

264
00:15:37,374 --> 00:15:38,876
-It's Chi-ho.
<i>-It's Chi-ho.</i>

265
00:15:38,959 --> 00:15:41,086
-What's the password?
<i>-What's the password?</i>

266
00:15:41,170 --> 00:15:42,337
Nice.

267
00:15:42,421 --> 00:15:43,964
Wow.

268
00:15:46,133 --> 00:15:49,219
-Okay, then. I'll call Jang Seong-gu now.
-I'm a bit nervous.

269
00:15:49,303 --> 00:15:51,430
Don't be nervous. Just act natural.

270
00:15:54,058 --> 00:15:55,184
<i>Hello?</i>

271
00:15:56,226 --> 00:15:57,269
It's me, Chi-ho.

272
00:15:57,352 --> 00:16:00,314
I'd appreciate it
if you could give me the password.

273
00:16:00,981 --> 00:16:02,274
<i>Is this really Chi-ho?</i>

274
00:16:02,357 --> 00:16:04,568
<i>You don't sound like yourself.</i>

275
00:16:04,651 --> 00:16:05,861
<i>-Who is this?</i>
-Let me.

276
00:16:09,573 --> 00:16:12,451
You fucking asshole, who else would I be?
Goddamn idiot.

277
00:16:12,534 --> 00:16:13,660
Give me the password.

278
00:16:13,744 --> 00:16:16,663
<i>It's Wi-Fi. "Wi-Fi" in Korean.</i>

279
00:16:25,422 --> 00:16:28,634
The account belongs to Seong-gu,
but he doesn't have his own profile.

280
00:16:28,717 --> 00:16:31,762
They've been sharing the same account.

281
00:16:31,845 --> 00:16:34,056
I checked Seong-gu's food delivery app,

282
00:16:34,139 --> 00:16:36,391
and he's had deliveries
to several addresses.

283
00:16:36,475 --> 00:16:38,560
There were even orders over 100,000 won.

284
00:16:38,644 --> 00:16:40,938
He's subscribed to more than 20 games.

285
00:16:41,021 --> 00:16:43,607
That's impossible
unless all he does is play games.

286
00:16:43,690 --> 00:16:45,943
He had a lot of charges
for e-scooter rentals too.

287
00:16:46,610 --> 00:16:48,028
It says he's on one right now.

288
00:16:48,112 --> 00:16:50,989
It says the food just got delivered.

289
00:16:51,824 --> 00:16:53,951
He just logged into a game too.

290
00:16:54,034 --> 00:16:56,703
Are you saying
Jang Seong-gu is on a scooter,

291
00:16:56,787 --> 00:17:00,165
eating with one hand
and playing a game with the other?

292
00:17:12,302 --> 00:17:15,097
Do you really need to picture it?
It's obviously impossible.

293
00:17:15,180 --> 00:17:17,057
Money isn't the real problem, is it?

294
00:17:17,141 --> 00:17:19,309
What about the scam cases you looked into?

295
00:17:20,727 --> 00:17:24,606
There's a website
where scam victims share information.

296
00:17:24,690 --> 00:17:26,150
I looked up Seong-gu's user ID,

297
00:17:26,233 --> 00:17:29,611
and it showed reports of undelivered items
and fake sales on resale apps.

298
00:17:29,695 --> 00:17:31,113
They were all scam-related.

299
00:17:31,196 --> 00:17:33,323
The punks used Seong-gu's ID
to post fake items,

300
00:17:33,407 --> 00:17:35,868
then took the money
and ghosted the buyers.

301
00:17:35,951 --> 00:17:39,246
Isn't this way too much
for just one kid to deal with on his own?

302
00:17:55,095 --> 00:17:56,096
The goddamn scammer.

303
00:17:57,306 --> 00:17:59,516
You scammed me over the AirPods,
didn't you?

304
00:17:59,600 --> 00:18:02,186
No, it wasn't me. I really didn't do it.

305
00:18:02,269 --> 00:18:04,062
Some kids stole my account.

306
00:18:04,146 --> 00:18:06,398
-Really, I didn't--
-You son of a bitch.

307
00:18:06,899 --> 00:18:08,483
It really wasn't me.

308
00:18:08,567 --> 00:18:13,071
You fucking asshole, you asked for it.
You bastard.

309
00:18:13,155 --> 00:18:14,489
You goddamn bastard.

310
00:18:14,573 --> 00:18:17,034
You little shit, trying to pull scams?
You wanna die?

311
00:18:17,117 --> 00:18:19,912
You goddamn thief.
Give me my money back, you bastard.

312
00:18:21,830 --> 00:18:22,706
Damn.

313
00:18:25,042 --> 00:18:27,669
You idiot. Why'd you get caught?

314
00:18:33,675 --> 00:18:36,428
He said I'll be sorry
if I don't pay him back.

315
00:18:37,095 --> 00:18:37,930
And?

316
00:18:38,013 --> 00:18:41,308
Chi-ho, I'm really sorry,
but I don't have any money.

317
00:18:41,391 --> 00:18:43,852
-If you could help out a bit--
-That's too bad.

318
00:18:44,353 --> 00:18:46,230
I've run out of allowance too.

319
00:18:46,730 --> 00:18:48,815
You take care of it, okay?

320
00:18:49,399 --> 00:18:50,275
Chi-ho.

321
00:18:51,568 --> 00:18:52,611
Please, I'm asking you.

322
00:18:52,694 --> 00:18:54,196
For God's sake.

323
00:18:56,031 --> 00:18:58,283
I said I'd deal with it later.

324
00:18:58,367 --> 00:18:59,868
Yeah, but when?

325
00:19:01,912 --> 00:19:03,121
Should I break my promise?

326
00:19:05,332 --> 00:19:07,542
No, keep your promise.

327
00:19:07,626 --> 00:19:10,754
Do you know what would happen
if I changed my mind?

328
00:19:10,837 --> 00:19:13,840
Everything is under your account
and your name, okay?

329
00:19:13,924 --> 00:19:15,425
You'll be the one who's fucked.

330
00:19:15,509 --> 00:19:17,886
But I told you
I'd deal with everything later.

331
00:19:19,388 --> 00:19:20,389
Super grateful, right?

332
00:19:23,725 --> 00:19:25,519
<i>My son tells me</i>

333
00:19:25,602 --> 00:19:30,315
your son uses my son's account
to order food and spend money on games.

334
00:19:31,984 --> 00:19:34,945
Take a look.
Hundreds of thousands of won were charged.

335
00:19:35,779 --> 00:19:38,365
That's your side of the story.

336
00:19:38,448 --> 00:19:41,493
I told Chi-ho to come home now,
so let's hear his side too.

337
00:19:44,705 --> 00:19:45,872
There you are.

338
00:19:46,373 --> 00:19:47,416
Hey, Jang Seong-gu.

339
00:19:47,916 --> 00:19:49,543
Go. It's okay.

340
00:19:50,794 --> 00:19:52,296
You sent this crap to my sister?

341
00:19:56,717 --> 00:19:57,968
You DMed her.

342
00:19:58,051 --> 00:20:00,012
Oh my God, what is this?

343
00:20:00,095 --> 00:20:03,348
Seong-gu, did you really send her this?

344
00:20:03,432 --> 00:20:05,142
Mom, I didn't do this.

345
00:20:05,225 --> 00:20:07,853
-It's Chi-ho. He did this too.
-Excuse me?

346
00:20:07,936 --> 00:20:10,647
Are you saying Chi-ho sent this
to his own sister?

347
00:20:10,731 --> 00:20:12,107
Does that make any sense?

348
00:20:12,190 --> 00:20:13,150
Are you crazy?

349
00:20:13,817 --> 00:20:16,486
-I should call the police. Unbelievable.
-Mom.

350
00:20:16,570 --> 00:20:17,779
No, wait.

351
00:20:18,280 --> 00:20:19,406
I'm sorry.

352
00:20:19,489 --> 00:20:22,659
If this offended you,
I apologize on his behalf.

353
00:20:22,743 --> 00:20:24,244
Please forgive him this once.

354
00:20:24,328 --> 00:20:26,413
-Next time…
-This will never happen again.

355
00:20:26,496 --> 00:20:29,458
…I'll send it to every girl in our class
using your account.

356
00:20:29,541 --> 00:20:31,835
-Snitch on me again, dumbass.
-They're only kids.

357
00:20:33,795 --> 00:20:36,882
-Ji-ho, you okay?
-Please forget why I came. I'm so…

358
00:20:36,965 --> 00:20:38,675
Hey, I'm so sorry. All right?

359
00:20:39,760 --> 00:20:40,761
-Go.
-Are you insane?

360
00:20:40,844 --> 00:20:42,179
Mom, it wasn't me.

361
00:20:42,262 --> 00:20:43,555
Be quiet, you fool.

362
00:20:43,638 --> 00:20:45,140
-Mom, it wasn't me.
-I'm sorry.

363
00:20:45,223 --> 00:20:47,601
Are you okay, Ji-ho?

364
00:20:50,937 --> 00:20:51,772
Yeah.

365
00:20:52,647 --> 00:20:53,565
Thanks.

366
00:20:54,441 --> 00:20:56,401
All right.

367
00:20:59,696 --> 00:21:02,783
Chi-ho, do you mind if I take a call?

368
00:21:02,866 --> 00:21:04,826
Can't you see I'm playing a game?

369
00:21:04,910 --> 00:21:06,828
It's going to lag.

370
00:21:06,912 --> 00:21:07,746
It's my mom.

371
00:21:08,955 --> 00:21:10,082
Damn it.

372
00:21:10,582 --> 00:21:11,416
Answer, idiot.

373
00:21:15,295 --> 00:21:16,213
Hello?

374
00:21:16,296 --> 00:21:18,882
<i>What the hell have you been up to?</i>

375
00:21:20,592 --> 00:21:21,968
How much is all this?

376
00:21:22,052 --> 00:21:22,886
FOODMON ORDER HISTORY

377
00:21:22,969 --> 00:21:26,264
When I paid this off for you before,
I said that was the last time.

378
00:21:26,348 --> 00:21:28,600
How many times is this now?

379
00:21:28,683 --> 00:21:31,561
How am I supposed to make sense of this?

380
00:21:33,438 --> 00:21:37,692
Jang Seong-gu. Don't you have
anything to say to me? Well?

381
00:21:38,193 --> 00:21:39,986
Don't tell me it was your friend again.

382
00:21:40,070 --> 00:21:41,780
It really wasn't me.

383
00:21:41,863 --> 00:21:44,699
After all that humiliation last time,
you're lying again?

384
00:21:46,159 --> 00:21:49,663
Why are you growing up like this?
What's suddenly gotten into you?

385
00:21:51,832 --> 00:21:52,833
Seriously…

386
00:22:32,038 --> 00:22:35,917
Seong-gu wants to tell you everything
Lee Chi-ho has done to him.

387
00:22:37,169 --> 00:22:38,462
You'll tell him, right?

388
00:22:40,839 --> 00:22:41,673
Yes.

389
00:22:42,299 --> 00:22:44,050
I'll tell you everything.

390
00:22:45,135 --> 00:22:47,679
He says I can trust the ERPB.

391
00:22:55,687 --> 00:22:58,023
<i>Do you think</i>
<i>the ERPB won't believe you either?</i>

392
00:23:05,071 --> 00:23:07,491
If the ERPB had existed two years ago

393
00:23:08,450 --> 00:23:10,202
and had come

394
00:23:11,953 --> 00:23:13,079
to our school…

395
00:23:18,210 --> 00:23:20,795
I wouldn't have killed anyone…

396
00:23:22,964 --> 00:23:25,050
and no one would've died.

397
00:23:25,926 --> 00:23:28,178
Inspector Na Hwa-jin will be different.

398
00:23:29,846 --> 00:23:31,973
He's just like Ms. Choi.

399
00:23:38,146 --> 00:23:40,607
HE USED MY IDENTITY ON VARIOUS WEBSITES
TO SCAM PEOPLE

400
00:23:42,108 --> 00:23:43,151
Yes.

401
00:23:45,195 --> 00:23:46,196
Inspector.

402
00:23:46,696 --> 00:23:51,868
Well, did you hear about
the School Violence Committee meeting?

403
00:23:54,120 --> 00:23:59,084
Chi-ho reported Seong-gu for bullying.

404
00:24:00,252 --> 00:24:01,086
What?

405
00:24:08,510 --> 00:24:10,679
SCHOOL VIOLENCE DELIBERATION COMMITTEE

406
00:24:12,973 --> 00:24:15,809
VICTIM STUDENT

407
00:24:15,892 --> 00:24:19,020
ACCUSED STUDENT

408
00:24:23,191 --> 00:24:24,651
Just a moment.

409
00:24:25,360 --> 00:24:28,405
An ERPB inspector cannot legally serve
on the committee.

410
00:24:28,488 --> 00:24:29,489
Please have him leave.

411
00:24:29,573 --> 00:24:33,243
We also received a report
and have been monitoring the situation,

412
00:24:33,910 --> 00:24:36,329
so we need to understand what happened.

413
00:24:36,413 --> 00:24:38,206
I'll simply observe.

414
00:24:38,290 --> 00:24:39,541
Speaking is not permitted.

415
00:24:40,166 --> 00:24:41,001
Yes, sir.

416
00:24:42,002 --> 00:24:46,339
All right. We will now begin
the review of the school violence case

417
00:24:46,423 --> 00:24:47,757
at Jinwon High School.

418
00:24:47,841 --> 00:24:51,219
First, we will hear the statement
from the victim's side.

419
00:24:51,303 --> 00:24:53,722
Even before the incident
was fully investigated,

420
00:24:53,805 --> 00:24:56,975
Jang Seong-gu spread false rumors
about Lee Chi-ho

421
00:24:57,058 --> 00:25:00,979
and called in the ERPB,
effectively branding him as the bully.

422
00:25:01,062 --> 00:25:03,231
He is in severe psychological distress.

423
00:25:03,315 --> 00:25:06,901
His psychiatric treatment records
are hereby submitted as evidence.

424
00:25:11,865 --> 00:25:13,992
DEPRESSIVE DISORDER
PANIC DISORDER

425
00:25:14,826 --> 00:25:17,787
Next, we will hear from the accused.
Please make your statement.

426
00:25:22,292 --> 00:25:23,627
Oh, I…

427
00:25:31,343 --> 00:25:32,510
This isn't fair.

428
00:25:35,180 --> 00:25:37,891
I'm the victim here.

429
00:25:40,352 --> 00:25:43,188
They stole my accounts.

430
00:25:44,147 --> 00:25:46,650
They used them to run scams,

431
00:25:46,733 --> 00:25:47,817
play games,

432
00:25:48,693 --> 00:25:49,944
and order food.

433
00:25:50,028 --> 00:25:51,404
Is there any evidence?

434
00:25:53,281 --> 00:25:55,575
Do you have any evidence
that they stole your accounts?

435
00:25:56,576 --> 00:25:57,827
Well, that's--

436
00:25:57,911 --> 00:26:00,497
As you can see, his claim is one-sided
with no evidence.

437
00:26:01,164 --> 00:26:03,958
We cannot rule out
that he might be making false statements.

438
00:26:04,042 --> 00:26:06,628
If so, it could constitute defamation.

439
00:26:19,974 --> 00:26:22,477
You'll see if you look at the records.

440
00:26:22,560 --> 00:26:25,271
I'm online at an Internet café
while on an e-scooter

441
00:26:25,355 --> 00:26:27,941
and having food delivered elsewhere.
If you see the logs--

442
00:26:28,024 --> 00:26:29,150
That's right.

443
00:26:29,234 --> 00:26:32,612
Lee Chi-ho said he borrowed his accounts
a few times for urgent reasons.

444
00:26:32,696 --> 00:26:33,863
It wasn't a few times--

445
00:26:33,947 --> 00:26:35,323
Only answer

446
00:26:36,991 --> 00:26:38,201
what you're asked.

447
00:26:41,413 --> 00:26:44,541
Once or twice, Chi-ho borrowed
his streaming service account

448
00:26:44,624 --> 00:26:47,001
and used his account
to rent a bike a few times.

449
00:26:47,085 --> 00:26:48,294
That's all.

450
00:26:48,378 --> 00:26:53,383
And yet, Chi-ho wanted to help his friend
and sent Jang Seong-gu money.

451
00:26:53,466 --> 00:26:55,218
I never received any money.

452
00:26:55,301 --> 00:26:57,095
Please check your bank account.

453
00:27:04,269 --> 00:27:05,478
SEJIN TRANSACTION ACCOUNT

454
00:27:05,562 --> 00:27:07,814
LEE CHI-HO / REPAYMENT
DEPOSIT 1,000,000 WON

455
00:27:16,406 --> 00:27:17,490
By contrast,

456
00:27:17,574 --> 00:27:20,577
the harm Lee Chi-ho has suffered
is very serious.

457
00:27:20,660 --> 00:27:22,954
Deemed a bully, based on unfounded claims,

458
00:27:23,037 --> 00:27:24,998
he is being shunned
and isolated at school.

459
00:27:25,081 --> 00:27:27,751
But what's more concerning
is that this false narrative

460
00:27:27,834 --> 00:27:30,128
is even threatening Chi-ho's future.

461
00:27:30,211 --> 00:27:32,505
This is not simply defamation.

462
00:27:32,589 --> 00:27:34,340
It is social character assassination.

463
00:27:35,300 --> 00:27:38,428
Of course, we do not intend
to pursue criminal charges.

464
00:27:38,511 --> 00:27:41,181
However, we have submitted
the psychiatric records,

465
00:27:41,681 --> 00:27:43,892
and given his struggles
to keep up with studies,

466
00:27:43,975 --> 00:27:48,646
we believe an appropriate mediation,
compensation, or settlement is needed.

467
00:27:48,730 --> 00:27:50,190
A settlement?

468
00:27:51,775 --> 00:27:52,734
How much…

469
00:27:53,568 --> 00:27:57,447
That said,
since it's a matter between children,

470
00:27:57,530 --> 00:27:59,532
Chi-ho's mother, a truly admirable woman,

471
00:27:59,616 --> 00:28:03,203
wishes to receive an apology
and settle the matter here.

472
00:28:04,120 --> 00:28:06,372
What do you say, Seong-gu's mother?

473
00:28:14,923 --> 00:28:16,508
Chi-ho's mother.

474
00:28:18,092 --> 00:28:19,344
Thank you so much.

475
00:28:20,512 --> 00:28:22,847
I'll make sure this never happens again.

476
00:28:22,931 --> 00:28:26,017
I really appreciate your leniency.

477
00:28:26,518 --> 00:28:27,727
Chi-ho.

478
00:28:28,228 --> 00:28:29,854
I'm sorry, all right?

479
00:28:30,522 --> 00:28:32,148
I'm really sorry.

480
00:28:32,649 --> 00:28:33,691
My goodness, ma'am…

481
00:28:35,276 --> 00:28:36,528
<i>So that's the situation.</i>

482
00:28:37,570 --> 00:28:38,863
Understood, sir.

483
00:28:43,034 --> 00:28:44,369
Can you believe this?

484
00:28:44,869 --> 00:28:46,955
He did wrong,
yet he calls for the meeting.

485
00:28:47,038 --> 00:28:49,415
He even hired an expensive lawyer!

486
00:28:50,333 --> 00:28:55,255
These days, I hear lawyers specializing
in school bullying provide manuals.

487
00:28:56,130 --> 00:28:59,676
"File a complaint first.
That way, you can claim victim status."

488
00:28:59,759 --> 00:29:02,929
"File a counter-report.
That's how it turns into mutual fault."

489
00:29:03,012 --> 00:29:04,222
They say things like this.

490
00:29:04,305 --> 00:29:06,891
But still,
what's the School Violence Committee for?

491
00:29:07,392 --> 00:29:10,270
It should be able to determine the truth!

492
00:29:10,353 --> 00:29:13,273
But it's not that easy in reality.

493
00:29:13,356 --> 00:29:17,235
They have to review the case,
meet the students briefly,

494
00:29:17,318 --> 00:29:19,362
and reach a decision all on the same day.

495
00:29:19,445 --> 00:29:21,906
Since that's difficult,
they just look at the evidence,

496
00:29:21,990 --> 00:29:24,951
but they struggle
to decide who is at fault,

497
00:29:25,451 --> 00:29:28,705
handing down
similar rulings over and over.

498
00:29:28,788 --> 00:29:30,331
What should we do?

499
00:29:30,832 --> 00:29:32,584
Damn it, what are we going to do?

500
00:29:54,522 --> 00:29:56,441
SEONG-GU'S IPHONE

501
00:30:06,492 --> 00:30:08,119
SEONG-GU'S IPHONE, WEAK CONNECTION

502
00:30:17,378 --> 00:30:22,050
SEONG-GU'S IPHONE, STRONG CONNECTION

503
00:30:53,164 --> 00:30:54,415
There you are.

504
00:31:24,821 --> 00:31:26,990
It's okay to cry out loud, Seong-gu.

505
00:31:27,991 --> 00:31:29,492
Why are you holding it in?

506
00:31:35,081 --> 00:31:37,041
If you hold it in,

507
00:31:38,334 --> 00:31:39,919
no one will know you're crying.

508
00:31:42,380 --> 00:31:44,048
If you don't speak up,

509
00:31:44,841 --> 00:31:46,884
no one will know you've been wronged.

510
00:31:48,720 --> 00:31:52,765
And if you're curled up like this,
they'll never know what they did wrong.

511
00:31:59,397 --> 00:32:00,898
Is this how you want to live?

512
00:32:16,789 --> 00:32:18,791
All right, then.

513
00:32:30,845 --> 00:32:32,305
