I know you're fine. You're not even sick.

774
00:45:26,495 --> 00:45:28,413
-Look at him.
-Tell them.

775
00:45:28,497 --> 00:45:30,123
Tell them it's all a lie, an act.

776
00:45:30,207 --> 00:45:32,000
Like my son says, if it's an act…

777
00:45:35,212 --> 00:45:37,422
Stop it! Oh my goodness.

778
00:45:39,341 --> 00:45:40,759
How does it feel?

779
00:45:42,427 --> 00:45:44,388
Are you finally asking yourself,

780
00:45:44,972 --> 00:45:46,098
"Why did I do that?"

781
00:45:49,518 --> 00:45:51,728
Will it only sink in
if your finger gets broken?

782
00:45:51,812 --> 00:45:53,313
Oh my God, what's wrong with her?

783
00:45:53,397 --> 00:45:55,190
All right, Inspector Im Han-rim.

784
00:45:56,650 --> 00:45:57,609
Oh no, my son.

785
00:45:59,528 --> 00:46:01,989
Inspector Im Han-rim here

786
00:46:02,489 --> 00:46:05,826
is actually an ERPB field investigator
who was assigned

787
00:46:05,909 --> 00:46:08,412
to look into the bullying case
involving Jang Seong-gu.

788
00:46:09,037 --> 00:46:11,331
Right, so that's what's been going on.

789
00:46:12,499 --> 00:46:15,043
So why did we go to such lengths?

790
00:46:15,544 --> 00:46:18,839
It's because of Jang Seong-gu.

791
00:46:23,051 --> 00:46:24,386
Seong-gu!

792
00:46:25,971 --> 00:46:26,972
You see us, right?

793
00:46:39,318 --> 00:46:40,193
Yes.

794
00:46:40,819 --> 00:46:44,531
We are here to clear his name.

795
00:46:46,491 --> 00:46:47,701
How does it feel?

796
00:46:48,994 --> 00:46:51,955
Do you finally realize

797
00:46:52,497 --> 00:46:53,749
what you did to Seong-gu?

798
00:46:53,832 --> 00:46:56,209
This is really not fair.

799
00:46:57,669 --> 00:46:59,588
I never even laid a finger on Seong-gu.

800
00:46:59,671 --> 00:47:01,965
That's right. You never hit him.

801
00:47:02,591 --> 00:47:05,636
There's not a scratch on him.
But do you think it wasn't violence?

802
00:47:07,054 --> 00:47:09,473
You never touched him,

803
00:47:10,682 --> 00:47:12,893
yet he was scared, terrified,

804
00:47:12,976 --> 00:47:15,187
wronged, and frustrated.

805
00:47:15,687 --> 00:47:18,315
No one believed him,
no matter what he said.

806
00:47:18,815 --> 00:47:20,984
Not even his parents. That's right.

807
00:47:21,735 --> 00:47:24,154
He probably thought
it'd be better to be beaten.

808
00:47:24,237 --> 00:47:25,072
Why?

809
00:47:25,572 --> 00:47:27,532
Because if he had marks from it,

810
00:47:29,284 --> 00:47:31,203
his parents might believe him.

811
00:47:32,579 --> 00:47:34,247
<i>Do you know what's worse?</i>

812
00:47:34,790 --> 00:47:37,125
<i>To get out of the situation,</i>

813
00:47:37,209 --> 00:47:40,963
<i>he had no choice but to beg</i>
<i>the very person who put him there.</i>

814
00:47:41,046 --> 00:47:43,882
The victim had no choice
but to bow his head…

815
00:47:46,718 --> 00:47:48,971
and plead with the bully.

816
00:47:50,514 --> 00:47:52,307
This is what you did to Seong-gu.

817
00:47:53,100 --> 00:47:54,685
Without laying a finger on him.

818
00:48:03,026 --> 00:48:04,569
It's been hard for you, hasn't it?

819
00:48:05,153 --> 00:48:08,115
It must've been so hard, all on your own.

820
00:48:08,615 --> 00:48:10,909
Seong-gu, I'm sorry. All right?

821
00:48:11,410 --> 00:48:15,122
I was such a fool.

822
00:48:15,205 --> 00:48:17,916
I should've believed you.

823
00:48:21,586 --> 00:48:23,338
Our investigation found

824
00:48:23,922 --> 00:48:27,843
that Lee Chi-ho's testimony
about suffering harm

825
00:48:28,427 --> 00:48:30,929
because of Jang Seong-gu was false

826
00:48:31,013 --> 00:48:33,682
and that the actual victim
is Jang Seong-gu.

827
00:48:33,765 --> 00:48:35,809
Accordingly, the ERPB will implement

828
00:48:35,892 --> 00:48:39,396
appropriate protective measures
for the victim, Jang Seong-gu, at once.

829
00:48:39,479 --> 00:48:43,400
Additionally, the prior ruling against him
by the School Violence Committee

830
00:48:44,192 --> 00:48:48,113
will be fully nullified
by the authority of the ERPB.

831
00:48:51,116 --> 00:48:52,951
A victim is a victim.

832
00:48:53,660 --> 00:48:55,078
A bully is a bully.

833
00:48:57,456 --> 00:48:59,458
Is that so difficult?

834
00:49:06,298 --> 00:49:08,383
Adults should protect children.

835
00:49:10,177 --> 00:49:12,179
Aren't you ashamed to face them?

836
00:49:33,992 --> 00:49:36,203
Thank you for helping me.

837
00:49:36,286 --> 00:49:38,205
You'll be issued a new resident number.

838
00:49:38,789 --> 00:49:39,998
Do well at school.

839
00:49:40,082 --> 00:49:41,708
Thank you, sir.

840
00:49:41,792 --> 00:49:43,543
Thank you so much.

841
00:49:43,627 --> 00:49:44,795
It's finally over, ma'am.

842
00:49:44,878 --> 00:49:48,006
I'll make sure to raise Seong-gu well.

843
00:49:49,007 --> 00:49:50,425
Go home with your mother.

844
00:49:50,509 --> 00:49:51,343
Okay.

845
00:49:58,433 --> 00:49:59,267
Your friend?

846
00:49:59,851 --> 00:50:01,019
Well.

847
00:50:14,241 --> 00:50:15,242
I'm sorry.

848
00:50:15,826 --> 00:50:17,536
You told me not to do anything.

849
00:50:19,621 --> 00:50:20,580
But still,

850
00:50:20,664 --> 00:50:24,000
something good happened
because I did what I could.

851
00:50:25,168 --> 00:50:26,378
I'm glad.

852
00:50:48,400 --> 00:50:49,860
Welcome.

853
00:51:04,291 --> 00:51:06,001
Get your own glass.

854
00:51:06,501 --> 00:51:08,753
That's for Ga-yun.

855
00:51:39,993 --> 00:51:41,161
Lie down here.

856
00:51:42,370 --> 00:51:43,413
Careful.

857
00:52:03,767 --> 00:52:04,893
Hey.

858
00:52:06,895 --> 00:52:08,563
You should find another woman.

859
00:52:09,522 --> 00:52:10,357
Goodness.

860
00:52:12,067 --> 00:52:14,569
Ga-yun would be mad at me, you know?

861
00:52:15,612 --> 00:52:17,364
Imagine if she heard that.

862
00:52:19,199 --> 00:52:22,202
She'd go on at you
for a couple of hours at least.

863
00:52:22,827 --> 00:52:23,912
You know.

864
00:52:29,960 --> 00:52:30,877
God.

865
00:52:47,769 --> 00:52:49,354
<i>Busted.</i>

866
00:52:52,274 --> 00:52:53,191
No way.

867
00:52:57,612 --> 00:52:59,155
Fine, I won't smoke.

868
00:53:28,727 --> 00:53:29,728
<i>Here.</i>

869
00:53:30,478 --> 00:53:31,313
<i>Cheers!</i>

870
00:53:32,230 --> 00:53:34,816
Why would I toast with this guy?

871
00:53:35,900 --> 00:53:38,570
I don't toast with someone
who doesn't like me either.

872
00:53:43,325 --> 00:53:45,577
Are you really going to be like this?

873
00:53:45,660 --> 00:53:46,703
Yeah, I am.

874
00:53:46,786 --> 00:53:48,079
He leaves me no choice.

875
00:53:50,623 --> 00:53:51,458
Fine, then.

876
00:53:52,917 --> 00:53:53,877
I won't get married.

877
00:53:55,337 --> 00:53:57,005
Where'd that come from?

878
00:53:57,672 --> 00:53:58,506
Good.

879
00:53:58,590 --> 00:54:01,051
Yeah. But I'll never get married.

880
00:54:02,302 --> 00:54:04,179
-Never?
-Yeah.

881
00:54:04,763 --> 00:54:06,389
If I can't marry Hwa-jin,

882
00:54:06,473 --> 00:54:08,433
I'll just live alone
till I get old and die.

883
00:54:09,017 --> 00:54:12,228
Then, Dad, you'll never get to hold
your grandchild

884
00:54:12,312 --> 00:54:15,857
or hear them call you "Grandpa."
You'll just grow old.

885
00:54:16,358 --> 00:54:20,570
If you don't want that,
should you be acting like this or not?

886
00:54:21,154 --> 00:54:22,906
Well, that can't happen.

887
00:54:24,741 --> 00:54:28,286
Then do you think
you two should be toasting or not?

888
00:54:30,538 --> 00:54:31,373
Shall we?

889
00:54:32,332 --> 00:54:33,792
Make it a couples' shot.

890
00:54:33,875 --> 00:54:35,585
That's gross. Why would we do that?

891
00:54:35,668 --> 00:54:38,129
Then I won't get married.
Whatever. I'm recording.

892
00:54:38,213 --> 00:54:39,255
-Ga-yun, that's…
-Wait.

893
00:54:39,339 --> 00:54:40,465
-One…
-Hold on. Hey.

894
00:54:40,548 --> 00:54:41,383
Two…

895
00:54:41,466 --> 00:54:42,759
Three!

896
00:56:12,432 --> 00:56:14,058
For fuck's sake.

897
00:56:14,642 --> 00:56:15,477
Hey.

898
00:56:16,227 --> 00:56:17,061
Damn it.

899
00:56:18,688 --> 00:56:20,482
You said I'd win.

900
00:56:20,565 --> 00:56:22,650
You said if I got a lawyer,
it'd be game over.

901
00:56:27,572 --> 00:56:29,073
File a report first.

902
00:56:29,574 --> 00:56:30,825
Why should I?

903
00:56:31,326 --> 00:56:32,160
What for?

904
00:56:32,243 --> 00:56:35,330
I don't think you can afford
to be this relaxed right now.

905
00:56:36,039 --> 00:56:40,877
The ERPB will do everything they can
to brand you as the bully.

906
00:56:41,377 --> 00:56:43,046
Then you'll at least get suspended.

907
00:56:43,129 --> 00:56:44,047
No,

908
00:56:44,923 --> 00:56:46,132
you may even get expelled.

909
00:56:50,386 --> 00:56:52,305
You need to lay the groundwork first.

910
00:56:53,223 --> 00:56:55,808
The first one to file
becomes the victim in today's world.

911
00:56:56,976 --> 00:57:00,438
If you don't want to be branded
as the bully, act like the victim.

912
00:57:01,689 --> 00:57:03,107
This person will help you.

913
00:57:03,608 --> 00:57:05,026
ATTORNEY YOON TAE-GYEONG

914
00:57:06,110 --> 00:57:07,529
<i>Now what?</i>

915
00:57:08,821 --> 00:57:12,200
-I think everything went as planned.
-Fucking hell.

916
00:57:12,700 --> 00:57:15,370
What the fuck are you talking about?

917
00:57:17,288 --> 00:57:19,874
Hey, my life's over because of the ERPB.

918
00:57:21,042 --> 00:57:23,086
It's over for my family because of me.

919
00:57:23,169 --> 00:57:25,838
I feel like I have to fucking die
to end this.

920
00:57:27,715 --> 00:57:30,051
So how can you say it went as planned?
You bastard.

921
00:57:31,386 --> 00:57:33,888
I reported you to the ERPB
for bullying Jang Seong-gu

922
00:57:34,556 --> 00:57:36,266
so they would come after you.

923
00:57:37,850 --> 00:57:39,352
Do you know what happens next?

924
00:57:40,687 --> 00:57:41,521
This.

925
00:57:53,032 --> 00:57:55,785
MIRAE DAEHAN PARTY

926
00:57:55,868 --> 00:57:57,287
Sir.

927
00:58:00,164 --> 00:58:01,332
Have you seen this?

928
00:58:01,833 --> 00:58:03,710
The ERPB is in serious trouble.

929
00:58:03,793 --> 00:58:06,921
Something happened
while they were at Jinwon High.

930
00:58:11,467 --> 00:58:13,303
Sir, you have a visitor.

931
00:58:13,386 --> 00:58:14,220
Let them in.

932
00:58:15,305 --> 00:58:16,139
Well.

933
00:58:17,557 --> 00:58:19,851
What brings you here at this hour?

934
00:58:22,020 --> 00:58:22,854
Have a seat.

935
00:58:22,937 --> 00:58:23,771
Okay.

936
00:58:23,855 --> 00:58:26,190
Please bring us some tea.

937
00:58:27,191 --> 00:58:28,026
Sure.

938
00:58:29,068 --> 00:58:33,656
Wait, shouldn't you be on your way
to school right now?

939
00:58:33,740 --> 00:58:35,617
I have something to give you.

940
00:58:35,700 --> 00:58:37,702
I'll be on my way after I give you this.

941
00:58:37,785 --> 00:58:40,121
I can't miss school.

942
00:58:43,291 --> 00:58:45,209
<i>My life's over because of the ERPB.</i>

943
00:58:45,835 --> 00:58:47,545
<i>It's over for my family because of me.</i>

944
00:58:47,629 --> 00:58:50,465
<i>I feel like I have to fucking die</i>
<i>to end this.</i>

945
00:58:52,800 --> 00:58:54,969
What is this?

946
00:58:56,054 --> 00:58:57,055
It's what you wanted.

947
00:59:00,058 --> 00:59:01,392
Oh, it's okay.

948
00:59:01,476 --> 00:59:03,102
There were no cameras.

949
00:59:07,440 --> 00:59:09,067
It's not that I don't trust you.

950
00:59:10,401 --> 00:59:13,029
You can decide how you want to use it.

951
00:59:21,996 --> 00:59:24,666
STUDENT FALLS FROM JINWON HIGH ROOFTOP
SUICIDE SUSPECTED

952
00:59:26,084 --> 00:59:26,918
Hey.

953
00:59:28,586 --> 00:59:30,880
What the hell did you do?

954
00:59:31,547 --> 00:59:33,633
You think I got you out
so you could do this?

955
00:59:35,093 --> 00:59:36,094
Oh.

956
00:59:37,220 --> 00:59:38,304
That's not it.

957
00:59:40,890 --> 00:59:43,017
You didn't get me out.

958
00:59:44,352 --> 00:59:46,229
I planned all of this.

959
00:59:49,982 --> 00:59:50,817
What?

960
00:59:50,900 --> 00:59:53,069
You didn't drag me into this.

961
00:59:53,152 --> 00:59:55,363
I dragged you into it.

962
00:59:56,072 --> 00:59:58,783
I sent Officer Kang to you.

963
01:00:17,260 --> 01:00:18,344
PAROLE REVIEW MATERIALS

964
01:00:20,138 --> 01:00:22,640
DEEMED SUITABLE FOR SOCIAL REINTEGRATION
THROUGH PAROLE

965
01:00:26,644 --> 01:00:31,274
It really helped that you pulled strings
with the parole board.

966
01:00:31,774 --> 01:00:32,608
Thank you.

967
01:00:34,152 --> 01:00:35,153
You little shit!

968
01:00:37,822 --> 01:00:38,906
Now, don't swear.

969
01:00:39,824 --> 01:00:42,702
If you want to be president,
you should keep your dignity.

970
01:00:44,912 --> 01:00:47,165
At the end of the day,
you and I are the same.

971
01:00:47,832 --> 01:00:50,209
We both want to bring down the ERPB.

972
01:01:23,701 --> 01:01:26,621
Minister, how is Lee Chi-ho doing
right now?

973
01:01:26,704 --> 01:01:28,748
-Have you seen him?
-It's Hwang Gi-tae.

974
01:01:28,831 --> 01:01:30,333
Are you here to see Lee Chi-ho?

975
01:01:30,416 --> 01:01:34,128
How do you respond to another incident
like this happening at Jinwon High?

976
01:01:34,212 --> 01:01:35,546
What's going on?

977
01:01:36,255 --> 01:01:38,633
Mr. Hwang, what brings you here?

978
01:01:38,716 --> 01:01:41,135
The entire country is in uproar
over this tragedy.

979
01:01:41,219 --> 01:01:42,303
How could I not come?

980
01:01:44,430 --> 01:01:46,224
For now, his treatment is the priority.

981
01:01:46,724 --> 01:01:47,558
You should leave.

982
01:01:47,642 --> 01:01:50,937
I don't think you're in a position
to be saying that.

983
01:01:58,986 --> 01:02:00,738
<i>My life's over because of the ERPB.</i>

984
01:02:01,531 --> 01:02:03,533
<i>It's over for my family because of me.</i>

985
01:02:03,616 --> 01:02:06,410
<i>I feel like I have to fucking die</i>
<i>to end this.</i>

986
01:02:09,121 --> 01:02:11,082
Do you honestly believe

987
01:02:11,582 --> 01:02:14,293
the ERPB played no part
in what happened to Lee Chi-ho?

988
01:02:17,713 --> 01:02:21,092
<i>The release of an audio clip</i>
<i>of a Jinwon High School student</i>

989
01:02:21,175 --> 01:02:23,886
<i>who allegedly attempted suicide</i>
<i>has shocked the public.</i>

990
01:02:23,970 --> 01:02:28,307
<i>The five-second clip</i>
<i>that is going viral on social media</i>

991
01:02:28,391 --> 01:02:32,770
<i>features the student's own voice</i>
<i>expressing resentment toward the ERPB.</i>

992
01:02:32,854 --> 01:02:35,064
<i>The police are focusing</i>
<i>their investigation</i>

993
01:02:35,147 --> 01:02:38,150
<i>on the clip's authenticity,</i>
<i>who recorded it,</i>

994
01:02:38,234 --> 01:02:39,735
<i>and how it was distributed.</i>

995
01:02:40,236 --> 01:02:42,655
<i>The political sphere</i>
<i>is also taking immediate action,</i>

996
01:02:42,738 --> 01:02:45,533
<i>calling for an urgent inquiry to determine</i>

997
01:02:45,616 --> 01:02:47,743
<i>whether there were</i>
<i>any unlawful acts or coercion</i>

998
01:02:47,827 --> 01:02:49,787
<i>during the ERPB's investigation.</i>

999
01:02:49,871 --> 01:02:51,038
JINWON HIGH SCHOOL

1000
01:04:52,410 --> 01:04:55,371
Subtitle translation by: Lisa Kim

